格言“'''散兵坑里没有无神论者'''”（There are no atheists in foxholes）表达了这样一种观点，即当人们面临巨大的[[压力|压力]]或[[恐惧|恐惧]]，例如战争时，人们将会相信一种超然的力量以求安慰<ref name=washpost-2007>{{cite news | title = No Atheists in Fox Holes | author = Thomas J. Reese, S.J. | authorlink = Thomas J. Reese | url = http://newsweek.washingtonpost.com/onfaith/panelists/thomas_j_reese/2007/05/no_atheist_in_fox_holes.html | publisher = Washington Post Company | date = May 31, 2007 | accessdate = 2010-03-03 | archive-date = 2010-01-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100105164005/http://newsweek.washingtonpost.com/onfaith/panelists/thomas_j_reese/2007/05/no_atheist_in_fox_holes.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。
== 起源 ==
这一格言的确切起源尚不清楚。可能出自威廉·J·克里尔（William J. Clear）[[中校|中校]]或威廉·凯西（William Casey）中校<ref>{{cite news | first=Henry | last=Cummins | title=Spiritual Point | publisher=[[British_Humanist_Association|British Humanist Association]] | url=http://www.humanism.org.uk/uploadedFiles/cms/store//Humanist_Groups//ATTACHMENTS/Spiritual%20Point1%20no%20photo.pdf#search=%22%22no%20atheists%20in%20foxholes%22%20Lieutenant-Colonel%22 | work= | accessdate=2008-11-27 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927172732/http://www.humanism.org.uk/uploadedFiles/cms/store//Humanist_Groups//ATTACHMENTS/Spiritual%20Point1%20no%20photo.pdf#search=%22%22no%20atheists%20in%20foxholes%22%20Lieutenant-Colonel%22 | archivedate=2007-09-27 }}</ref>，但一般相信出自记者[[厄尼·派尔|厄尼·派尔]]（Ernie Pyle）<ref>{{cite news | first= | last= | title=Oops! He Did It Again! Brokaw Repeats Canard, "There Are No Atheists In Foxholes" During NBC Evening News | date=2003-03-12 | publisher=[[American_Atheists|American Atheists]] | url=http://www.atheists.org/flash.line/atheist9.htm | work=Flashline | accessdate=2008-11-27 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20030314150208/http://www.atheists.org/flash.line/atheist9.htm | archivedate=2003-03-14 }}</ref><ref>Johnson, Chip.  [http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2006/03/06/BAGFOHIUKD1.DTL "GI turns to Islam to find God."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2006%2F03%2F06%2FBAGFOHIUKD1.DTL |date=20110917155011 }} San Francisco Chronical. Monday, March 6, 2006.  Accessed Nov-22-2009.</ref><ref>[http://www.christianitytoday.com/books/features/weblog/031117.html Books & Culture Weblog: Content & Context - Books & Culture<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{Wayback|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/books/features/weblog/031117.html |date=20081211220816 }}, [[Christianity_Today|Christianity Today]]</ref>。

